OL,3,CChannel Islanders declined credit
OL,4,Ccards as they do not have UK addresses
OL,6,FChannel Islanders are still struggling
OL,7,Fto obtain credit cards, as banks
OL,8,Fdecline their applications because
OL,9,Fthey do not have a UK address.
OL,11,FMultiple UK providers have stopped
OL,12,Fserving the islands due to challenges
OL,13,Faccessing a central database of
OL,14,Fpersonal information they need to
OL,15,Fverify applications.
OL,17,FIt follows the introduction of new
OL,18,Fring-fencing laws, which require
OL,19,Ffinance firms to keep their British
OL,20,Fand offshore operations separate.
